HEADWORD: Grocer
<hw>Gro"cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Formerly written
<ets>grosser</ets>, orig., one who sells by the <ets>gross</ets>, or
deals by wholesale, fr. F. <ets>grossier</ets>, marchand
<ets>grossier</ets>, fr. <ets>gros</ets> large, great. See
<er>Gross</er>.]</ety> <def>A trader who deals in foods such as meats,
dairy products, produce, tea, sugar, spices, coffee, fruits, and various
other commodities.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grocer's itch</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a disease
of the skin, caused by handling sugar and treacle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grocery</ent>⟦br⟧
